			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Necromancer Epic Quest Complete</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Gregorian</a> | 
		            6/5/2001 2:10:50 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Necromance Epic Quest Walkthrough<BR>
<BR>
Where:	Nektulos Forest <BR>
When:	Level 50 or Higher<BR>
Reward:	Scythe of the Shadowed Soul<BR>
	MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
	Skill: 1HB Atk Delay: 34<BR>
	DMG: 22<BR>
	+5 STR, +10 STA, +5 CHA, +20 INT, +20 HP, +80 MANA, +5 FR, +15 DR, +5 	CR, +10 MR, +15 PR<BR>
	Effect: Torment of Shadows<BR>
	WT: 5.0 Size: MEDIUM<BR>
	Class: NEC<BR>
	Race: HUM, ERU, DEF, GNM, IKS<BR>
<BR>
Stage 1:	Nektulos Forest<BR>
	This Quest Starts in Nektulos Forest, the Dark Elf city home of the Necromancers.  Located adjacent to East Commons and Lavastorm Mountains.  There is no Availible Druid port in this zone, although there is a active wizard spire.  Once in the Nektulos Forest zone you will need to seek oout Venenzi Oberzendi. She is located at approx. [ -1000, -700] near the river.  When Hailed she will tell you that she is gathering components for her master, Kazen Fe'cae. She will also mention that if you wish to become a great necromancer, to tell Kazen you wish to study the dark arts.<BR>
<BR>
Stage 2:	Lake Rathetear<BR>
	You will need to seek out Kazen Fe'cae who is located in the Lake Rathetear zone at approx.             [ 340, -1600].  Hail Kazen and say &quot;I Wish to study the Dark Arts&quot;  he will then proceed to tell you that if you bring him the head of Sir Edwin Motte, then you can becom Kazen's servant.<BR>
<BR>
Stage 3:	East Freeport<BR>
	Now it is time to seek out Sir Edwin Motte, he is located near the docks in East Freeport. Important note he is a Palladin which means he has Lay of Hands, not too many HP.  Once you have Killed Sir Edwin, Return his head to Kazen in Lake Rathetear for further instructions.<BR>
<BR>
Sir Edwin Motte<BR>
Type: General NPC<BR>
Race, Class: HUM, PAL<BR>
Level Range: 33 - 33<BR>
Hit Points: 1407<BR>
Hits For: Unknown<BR>
Monetary Loot: Unknown<BR>
Special Attack: Unknown<BR>
Spawn Time: Unknown<BR>
Magical weapon not required.<BR>
Is quest related.<BR>
Is not aggressive.<BR>
Is not undead.<BR>
Last Updated: 02/26/01<BR>
<BR>
Stage 4: Lake Rathetear, Nektulos Forest, Lake Rathetear<BR>
	Now that you have Killed Sir Edwin Motte, return his head to Kazen and he will reward you with the Symbol of the Apprentice, and instruct you to once again visit Venenzi Oberendi in Nektulos Forest. Hand Her the Symbol of the Apprentice and she will hand you back the Twisted Symbol of the Apprentice.  She will also ask for a Flowing Black Robe for which she will had you back some Moss...  the Flowing Black Robes can be easily purchased in East Commons for usually 200pp or less.. or you can go to Najena and camp Najena Herself  for this robe.  Najena is Approx. Level 30.  The items you recieve from Venenzi Oberendi are to be given to Emkel Kabae in Lake Rathetear. Emkel is located near the stone Towers in Lake Rathetear.  Hand him the Twisted Symbol of the Apprentice and the Moss and he will give you the Symbol of the Serpent.  He will then tell you that more regents are needed and for you to head to The Swamp of No Hope in Kunark and locate Ssessthrass. <BR>
Najena<BR>
Type: MOB<BR>
Race, Class: DEF, MAG<BR>
Level Range: 30 - 30<BR>
Hit Points: Unknown<BR>
Hits For: Unknown<BR>
Monetary Loot: Unknown<BR>
Special Attack: Unknown<BR>
Spawn Time: 19 minutes<BR>
Magical weapon not required.<BR>
Is not quest related.<BR>
Is not aggressive.<BR>
Is not undead.<BR>
Last Updated: 11/01/00<BR>
<BR>
Stage 5: Swamp of No Hope<BR>
	The Swamp of No Hope is part of the Kunark Expansion.  The Swamp is adjacent to the following zones, Traks Teeth, East Cabilis, The Field of Bone, Fironia Vie. You are to locate Ssessthrass located at approx. [3800, 1600] and to hand him the Symbol of the Serpent. For which he will give you the Scaled Symbol of the Serpent, and tell you that the Manisi Herb you seek can be found guarded by the Royal Sanark in Chardok.<BR>
<BR>
Stage 6: Cahrdok<BR>
	Head off to Chardok in search of the Manisi Herb which can be found as a drop off the Royal Herbalist which spawns in the room with the secret entrance to Overking Bathezid's Room. Now heres where the hard stuff begins. The Royal Herbalist is a 33 minute spawn with a 1/6 variable ph list. At times there will be an Apprentice Herbalist, dont be confused, hes not the same thing and often times will drop nothing but some change. Chardok for those who dont know is a level 50+ zone, especially when your heading back twoards the Royals, anything lower then 50 is bait. Plan on going with at least 4 other groups and alot of hard work. I've had friends stuck on this part of the quest for months. Its a very rare spawn and an even more rare drop.  Once you have obtained the Manisi Herb head back to the Swamp of No Hope. Hand Ssessthrass the Manisi Herb and he will reward you with the Refined Manisi Herb which you need to take back to Emkel in Lake Rathetear.<BR>
<BR>
Stage 7: Lake Rathetear<BR>
	Head back to Lake Rathetear and hand Emkel the Refined Manisi Herb to be rewarded with the Symbol of Testing.  Once you have the Symbol of Testing Head over to Kazen.<BR>
Stage 8: Lake Rathetear<BR>
	Have about 12-15 people ready (clerics and tanks are a must) and give Symbol of Testing to Kazen. 3 mobs will spawn. Kill these, last drops symbol of Insanity. Yeah heres the reason why I started to do this. We did it with one group and it was really easy. Most all my friends are 55+ or close to. The golems do hit pretty hard and you might want to plan on a back up healer for the Cleric. If you went with 3 tanks, 1 Cleric, 1 healer type &amp; you with a pet the job will get done.<BR>
Stage 9: Timorous Deep, Plain of Air, Plain of Fear, Plain of Hate<BR>
	Take the Raft from Oasis to Timorous Deep to locate Drendico Metalbones which is near where the raft from Oasis drops you off at.   Hand him the Symbol of Insanity and he will give you his Journal and ask you for some more components. He will ask for the following items, Cloak of Spiroc Feathers, Eye of Innoruuk, and the Blood of Cazic Thule. <BR>
Blood of Cazic Thule is no longer found on Cazic Level 63, instead its a 50/50 chance on dropping, now found on Terror. A guardian of Cazic Thule, said to be the 2nd hardest mob in zone, looks like those iron guardians in Nektulos Forest. Also drops off of Dread Level 55 in the Plane of Fear. This one Can be Purchased if need be but is roughly 5kpp.<BR>
Slime Blood of Cazic Thule<BR>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <BR>
AC: 16<BR>
+2 AGI, +2 CHA, +2 DEX, +2 INT, +2 STA, +2 STR, +2 WIS, +20 HP, +20 MANA, +2 To All Saves<BR>
WT: 15.0 Size: ?<BR>
Class: ALL<BR>
Race: ALL<BR>
Avg Price: 5k pp<BR>
<BR>
Eye of Innoruuk is said to longer be dropped from Innoruuk, but there is no update as of now just who does drop this item. So I guess count on it being from the God himself till further notice. This also drops off the following Plane of Hate Mobs, Innoruuk Level 64, A Scorn Banshee Level 50, A Forsaken Revanent Level 50, and Maestro of Rancor Level 57. This one can Also be bought off of players but is prolly cheaper to go raid this guy..60k or less<BR>
Eye of Innoruuk<BR>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <BR>
AC: 5<BR>
+5 INT, +55 MANA, +10 MR<BR>
Effect: Chill Sight<BR>
WT: 1.5 Size: ?<BR>
Class: WIZ<BR>
Race: ALL<BR>
Avg Price: 60k pp<BR>
Cloak of Spiroc Feathers, You need a Silver Disc found pretty commonly on the second isle off of any mob. A Spiroc Feather found off the Spiroc's on the third isle, also fairly common. And the hardest part of this quest. The fourth isle's boss, Keeper of Souls Level 58-60, is the one you need to kill to complete the PoA quest. Level 60 mob boss, DT's (death touches) every 30 seconds. The cloak needed for the quest is said to be a 1/20 drop, but its more like 1/15. Heh, but with those ratios 5pt difference either way still doesnt spell fun. However he is possible to kill with just 18 people. The PoA Quest is as Follows: Talk to Drakis Bloodcaster who can be found in the Plane of Air. He will ask you if you are ready for the Test of Power. If you say yes, Jzil G'Six will appear to give you the quest details. Talk to him and he will ask you to retrieve three items for him to pass this test. Silver Disk Spiroc Feather Black Silk Cape Hand all three items back to Jzil and you will be rewarded with the Cloak of Spiroc Feathers. Sorry to say to all the necros out there with tons of Cash .. for this you must complete the quest yourself or multiquest it which i would assume would cost a pretty penny. This item is NO DROP and thus can only be Multi Quested or Camped. Unknown is if the indivudal items required for the Quest are No DROP or not.. if not then this quest would be a Cashers dream as far as easy of obtaining the items.<BR>
Cloak of Spiroc Feathers<BR>
LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
AC: 6<BR>
+5 INT, +6 STA +5 STR, +50 MANA<BR>
WT: 0.5 Size: ?<BR>
Class: NEC<BR>
Race: ALL<BR>
Stage 10: Timorous Deep, Lake Rathtear, Plain of Air<BR>
	Once you have obtained all three items, return to Drendico and hand him the Eye, Blood, Cloak and Journal and you'll be rewarded with the Prepared Reagents Box<BR>
Head back to Kazen in Lake Ratetear and hand him the Prepared Reagents Box and you'll receive the Tome of Instruction. Now off to the Plane of Air once more and hand the Thunder Spirit Princess 3pp. Clear the 3rd Island (Gorgalosk Island) and this will cause Gkzzallk to spawn. Hand him the Tome of Instruction and you'll be rewarded with the Gkzzallk in a Bottle.<BR>
Stage 11: Lake Rathetear<BR>
	Once you have the Gkzzallk in a Bottle head back to Lake Rathetear and Locate Kazen once again.. This time hand him the Gkzzallk in a Bottle and he will give you the <BR>
Scythe of the Shadowed Soul, the result of the Necromance Epic Quest.<BR>
Scythe of the Shadowed Soul<BR>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
Skill: 1HB Atk Delay: 34<BR>
DMG: 22<BR>
+5 STR, +10 STA, +5 CHA, +20 INT, +20 HP, +80 MANA, +5 FR, +15 DR, +5 CR, +10 MR, +15 PR<BR>
Effect: Torment of Shadows<BR>
WT: 5.0 Size: MEDIUM<BR>
Class: NEC<BR>
Race: HUM, ERU, DEF, GNM, IKS<BR>
<BR>
Stage 12: Conclusions<BR>
	Well now if you done this the easy yet expensive way you have to do what all of 4 battles in all ... but now what fun would that be... 3 if you were lucky enough to head to Chardok and /shout necro on epic.. anyone camping Herbalist , will Pay to loot the Manisi Herb =) .... but you prolly spent all of 100k pp or more by the tim you pay someone to multiquest the Cloak of Spiroc Feathers... but i guess some people have more pp then Lord Innoruuk himself.    but if you done this quest right you now have a sense of completeing the Necromancer Epic Quest, and are now the Proud Owner of a Duck Head on a Stick!<BR>
Happy Hunting Fellow Necromancers.<BR>
